# Frontend Standards

## TypeScript

- Use strict mode (already configured in tsconfig)
- Define types in `src/types/`
- Prefer interfaces for object shapes, types for unions

```typescript
// ✅ Define API types
interface Plan {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  createdAt: Date;
}

// ✅ Use explicit return types for complex functions
function calculateProjection(input: PlanInput): ProjectionResult {
  ...
}
```

## React Components

- Use functional components with hooks
- Place page components in `src/pages/`
- Place reusable components in `src/components/`
- Colocate component-specific logic

```tsx
// ✅ Component structure
export function InterviewPage() {
  const { messages, sendMessage } = useInterviewStore();
  
  return (
    <Layout>
      <ChatMessages messages={messages} />
      <ChatInput onSend={sendMessage} />
    </Layout>
  );
}
```

## State Management

- Use Zustand stores in `src/stores/`
- Keep stores focused on single domains
- Use React Query (`src/api/hooks.ts`) for server state

## Styling

- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Extract repeated patterns to components
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
